						<p>
				Hardware wallets must connect to a piece of software to give the user an interface to see token balances or create transactions. But the hardware wallet is responsible for signing the transactions (typically requiring a PIN) so that the private key is never stored on a computer connected to the internet.			</p>

						<p>
