						<p>
				A Defi wallet is a program designed to link users with the decentralized finance ecosystem. It can be used to store, send and receive cryptocurrency assets. DeFi wallets are non-custodial in nature, meaning the owner has complete control over the wallets and assets.			</p>

						<p>
				New to crypto? Users can choose to store their cryptocurrencies in Centralized exchanges (custodial wallet) or store cryptocurrencies using their own private keys and safeguarding their crypto assets by owning one of these DeFi wallets (non-custodial wallet). We've compiled some of the best wallets and which wallet to use with the different ecosystems that you'll be investing in.			</p>

						<p>
